  <brief_title>Vitamin D Treatment in Patients With Chronic Hepatitis C</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hillel Yaffe Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hillel Yaffe Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We hypothesize that patients with Ch.HCV have a low level of vitamin D, and that by raising
      their vitamin D levels by adding it to their standard treament of Pegylated Interferon and
      Ribavirin, there will be an increase in their sustained virological response.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
